ENTRY            G4120   20260422   20260528   20260528       G060
SUBENT        G4120001   20260422   20260528   20260528       G060
BIB                 16         31
TITLE      Study of the 67Cu activation in (gamma,p) -reaction
AUTHOR     (V.O.Zheltonozhsky,D.E.Myznikov,A.M.Savrasov,
           V.I.Slisenko, N.V.Kulich)
INSTITUTE  (4UKRIJD)
REFERENCE  (J,RPC,241,113533,2026)
           #doi:10.1016/j.radphyschem.2025.113533
FACILITY   (MICRT,4UKRIEP) The M-30 microtron
INC-SOURCE (BRST)
METHOD     (ACTIV) Induced gamma-activity was measured.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) The spectra were measured by two gamma
           spectrometers assembled on the basis of HPGe
           detectors from Canberra and Ortec. The energy
           resolution of both spectrometers was 1.9 keV on the
           gamma-line at 1332 keV, which accompanies the 60Co
           decay. The detection efficiency of the spectrometers
           was determined using the standard 152,154Eu and 133Ba
           calibration point sources.
SAMPLE     Assembly consisting of natural zinc and zirconium, and
           natural nickel and zirconium were irradiated. The
           metallic zirconium foils of natural isotopic
           composition near 1x1x0.01 cm in size and about 0.07 g
           in weight were used as a monitor targets. The purity
           all targets was near 99 %.
ADD-RES    Experimental data are compared with theoretical
           predictions calculated with TALYS-1.96 code.
MONITOR    (40-ZR-90(G,N)40-ZR-89,,SIG,,BRA)
DECAY-MON  (40-ZR-89-G,78.HR,DG,909.15)
MONIT-REF  (L0027012,A.Lepretre+,J,NP/A,175,609,1971)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information on sources of uncertainties.
STATUS     (TABLE,,V.O.Zheltonozhsky+,J,RPC,241,113533,2026) Tab.1
HISTORY    (20260422C) UkrNDC
